metadata.name: Duet #67
metadata.description:
by Daeinc
Aug 2022

Duet explores generative+computational motion and creates an almost infinite sequence of visual compositions. Two groups of shapes transform, merge, and split randomly. What can be disorienting starts to make sense as every element is animated from one to the other. This transition animation is what connects random pieces and creates a relationship between them. Each element is mathematically interpolated, with its motion defined by an equation. 

Although there are key moments, it is hard to summarize time-based work as a static image. As a constantly evolving generative motion piece, Duet invites viewers to form their impression by feeling the rhythm over time.

## Guide:
- The animation responds to window aspect ratio. It reproduces the same outcome at the same ratio. 
- For reliable playback, keep the window active and use IPFS view.
- See browser console for more info.
- Tested on MacOS 12.5.1 with Chromium 104.0

## Keyboard Interaction
- [n] to play a new random loop.
- [spacebar] to play/pause.
- [s] to save PNG. use URL params for dimensions.
- [up] and [down] to change shape resolution.
- [left] and [right] to change BPM. only works while looping. 
- [h] to toggle high DPI mode. off by default.
- [p] to toggle pixel snapping. off by default.

## URL Parameters
- add parameters separated by ampersand to the URL ex. https://.../?fxhash=...&w=1200&h=600
- [w] and [h]: set width and height in pixels. (ex. w=1200&h=600)
- [s] and [e]: set starting and ending keyframes (inclusive) for loop. (ex. s=20&e=24) 
- setting large values for start/end is not advised.
- [len]: instead of start/end, set a loop length between 1 and 16. (ex. len=4)
- [bpm]: beats per minute. (ex. bpm=80)
- [res]: shape resolution between 0 and 18. (ex. res=2)
- [pr]: pixel ratio. set it to 2 (or press [h]) for hi-DPI screens.
- [ar]: maximum aspect ratio. set to any value over 1. 1.2 by default.
- [snap]: add the param to snap to pixel grid.

## License
CC BY-NC 4.0
Please refer to the included LICENSE.md for license information.
Libraries used: canvas-sketch, canvas-sketch-util, dom-events, hsv2rgb, keyframes, equations from easings.net, array shuffle from stackoverflow.

metadata.name: Minima #261
metadata.description:
Minima is a study on focus and color. Playing with the idea of a simple composition of semicircles, either rotated up or down. The focus of the observer is moved with the use of gradual animation in the gradients and occasional circles and/or rectangles connecting the shapes together through color.

The name minima stems from the origins of the composition, mostly taking inspiration from minimalism in its use of a few elements to form a composition greater than the sum of its parts. Less is more, as they say.

The point at the bottom right of the canvas resembles the end of a sentence. Like reading a book, you process the canvas in a similar way, moving from what pops the most to what the least.

As the reader of this canvas I hope you observe what happens to your focus as the colors gradually move across the screen. The animations themselves are looping based on a noised sine wave, which gives them imperfections, imperfections you can observe.

----

Click / Tap on the bar at the bottom of the canvas to open up the GUI, used to export your minima into any format you want. Either .png or .svg. Ready for printing, if you desire.

ps. there might be a secret keyboard shortcut...

----

Minima,
Wouter Missler, 2022,
p5js + webgl.

metadata.name: Roasting Humans #210
metadata.description:
========
Concept
========
Humanists live in a world built on human bones.
The fuel of humanism is human sacrifices.

Eating flesh is natural for animals.
But humans are eating  life energy, results of work, time  of other humans.

Social status is in general about how many humans you personally can devour.
Personal freedom in general about how not to be eaten by other humans.

Sweet promises, beautiful concepts, inspiring ideas - basically ways to put  the victim on the skewer.

Humanism today is an attempt to inject anesthesia into the basic process of eating others.
Slavery must be gentle and invisible.
Weapons must be lethal and not cause suffering.
People should be polite and tolerant.
You must not feel that your blood is being sucked out.

If the victim does not feel the pain and does not scream: is the victim a plant? Is predator a vegan?

Is it better to you feel pain or inject anesthesia?
Anesthesia today is not only drugs, but entertainment.

Are you enjoy of eating others?
So check if you are on a skewer and how roasted you are.

==============
Technical Details
==============
Mangal size calculating depending on humans amount (min=5; max=111) and skewer parameters.

You can roast the bodies from different sides using the control buttons.
The bodies are divided into sectors that absorb thermal energy differently depending on the angle of rotation.
The amount of absorbed energy determines the degree of roasting.
The camera is focused on the active skewer, to select another one, press the button or select from the list.

Press the left mouse button to rotate the point of view.
Hold down the right mouse button to move the point of view.

metadata.name: Microreactors/A Box of Chocolates #41
metadata.description:
Objects drifting in a cell generate beautiful and complex patterns. They look like "Concentration fluctuations caused by thermal convection in microreactors". It also evokes Forrest Gump's famous line "Life is like a box of chocolates".

There is a phase difference between adjacent cells, generating similar but different patterns.

Each of them can be seen as a parallel world of life.

In addition, the observer can interfere with the pattern by clicking and dragging the mouse.

metadata.name: AngrySquares.gif #3
metadata.description:
An experiment in GIF serialization on fxhash by Nate Donato, this collection features a generative animation that can be automatically saved as a high quality gif.  Playing with block color and simple motion, each iteration features a rapid animation of basic shapes fluctuating under various different constraints.  The combined character of the full animation appears as an "angry" mass with pent up body motion and sharp color contrasting edges.  

Outputs can be programmatically saved to a high quality gif download, which can be used as a unique animated profile picture (*for any service that allows animated gif images)

Featuring:
x10 different possible color schemes (4 with near-infinite variations!)
x4 different possible generative weight classes (each with significant variation)
x3 different accent coloring styles (two with significant variation)
x7 different generalized anger levels (affecting animation speeds)
x6 possible special extra accent detail styles
x5 different base shape constructions
x1 'base' generative algorithm *

= 25,200 possible base feature combinations!!  Some traits and combinations are more likely to appear than others...

* Not included in calculations: a near infinite variety of shape positions, sizes, and placements, and a wide spectrum of possible animation lengths!


--


Keyboard controls:

Press [1] to view at native resolution
Press [2] to view at high resolution
Press [0] to scale to default screen width

Press [S] to save a high quality gif!* (May take a couple seconds to render)

*Tested in Google Chrome browser only!  
Should work in others but please use the latest version of Chrome if encountering any issue.
